<subSubSection id="C363AAB6FF8FC506FF12FEC9FE26FE73" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BC6F93DFF8FC506FF12FEC9FE26FE73" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FF12FEC9FEA0FF75" bold="true" box="[196,264,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FF12FEC9FEA8FF75" box="[196,256,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Faust's collection at 
<collectionCode id="ED6861F8FF8FC506FDFBFEC6FD2BFF76" box="[557,643,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">SMTD</collectionCode>
, a male fitting the description and with 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FBBCFEC6FB36FF76" box="[1130,1182,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
locality as “Biskra”, bearing the labels: [golden square label, indicating 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FCD3FEE3FCE2FF13" box="[773,842,189,215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
], “ 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FCBDFEE2FC29FF12" box="[875,897,188,214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
, Biskra, Bedel”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FBB7FEE3FA9CFF13" authority="Faust" authorityName="Faust" box="[1121,1332,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FBB7FEE3FB4DFF12" box="[1121,1253,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">rectirostris</emphasis>
Faust
</taxonomicName>
”, is here designated as the 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FEB2FEBCFE7BFF38" box="[356,467,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">lectotype</typeStatus>
, and has been labeled “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FD36FEBCFCC0FF38" box="[736,872,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FCA5FEBCFC21FF38" box="[883,905,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FC41FEBCFAB0FF38" authority="Faust, Gultekin" authorityName="Faust, Gultekin" box="[919,1304,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FC41FEBCFBF5FF3F" box="[919,1117,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Lixus rectirostris</emphasis>
Faust, Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FA82FEBCFA3AFF38" box="[1364,1426,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2008.0">2008</number>
” (
<figureCitation id="1342E5B8FF8FC506FF76FF56FEBCFEE6" box="[160,276,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,1122,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1122,1950]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 2. Lixus rectirostris Faust (Lectotypus); 1. dorsal view, 2. lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/294295/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FF32FF56FEBCFEE6" box="[228,276,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
). A female and a male, bearing the same labels above (a third lacks the golden square), are here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FEEBFF73FE42FE83" box="[317,490,301,327]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
, and have been labeled “ 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FCC7FF73FC6DFE83" box="[785,965,301,327]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Paralectotypus</typeStatus>
, Ƥ/ 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FC39FF72FBADFE82" box="[1007,1029,300,326]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FBC2FF73FA34FE83" authority="Faust, Gultekin" authorityName="Faust, Gultekin" box="[1044,1436,301,327]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FBC2FF73FB76FE82" box="[1044,1246,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Lixus rectirostris</emphasis>
Faust, Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FF1BFF0CFEA6FEA8" box="[205,270,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”. The 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FE8FFF0CFE6DFEA8" box="[345,453,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">lectotype</typeStatus>
was pinned through the right elytron and the elytra are weakly separated. The right funicle beyond the third segment, left funicle beyond the first segment and left fore tarsus beyond the second segment are missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363AAB6FF8FC506FF12FF9CFAE7FCC3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC6F93DFF8FC506FF12FF9CFAE7FCC3" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FF12FF9CFE95FE18" bold="true" box="[196,317,450,476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
The examination of 
<typeStatus id="54C2479FFF8FC506FDE3FF9CFDDBFE18" box="[565,627,450,476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">types</typeStatus>
of both species revealed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FC02FF9CFA28FE18" authority="Desbrochers, 1904" authorityName="Desbrochers" authorityYear="1904" box="[980,1408,450,476]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FC02FF9CFB33FE1F" box="[980,1179,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Lixus rectirostris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF8FC506FB72FF9CFA28FE18" author="Desbrochers" box="[1188,1408,450,476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" refString="Desbrochers, J. (1904) Etudes sur les Curculionides de la faune europeenne et des basins de la Mediterranee, en Afrique et en Asie, suivies des tableaux synoptiques. Le Frelon, 12 (5): 65 - 80, (6): 81 - 96, (7): 97 - 104." type="journal article" year="1904">
Desbrochers, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FA93FF9CFA28FE18" box="[1349,1408,450,476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FEA2FFB6FD47FDC6" authority="Faust, 1890" authorityName="Faust" authorityYear="1890" box="[372,751,488,514]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FEA2FFB6FDF9FDC5" box="[372,593,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Lixus rectirostris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF8FC506FD8CFFB6FD47FDC6" author="Faust" box="[602,751,488,514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" refString="Faust, J. (1890) Russelkafer aus den Mittelmeer-Landern. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1890 (2): 321 - 336." type="journal article" year="1890">
Faust, 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FD66FFB6FD47FDC6" box="[688,751,488,514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1890.0">1890</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and is also a junior homonym. Since the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FA8EFFB6FE89FDE2" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FA8EFFB6FE89FDE2" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Lixus rectirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was already employed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF8FC506FDA4FC53FCBCFDE3" author="Faust" box="[626,788,525,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" refString="Faust, J. (1890) Russelkafer aus den Mittelmeer-Landern. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1890 (2): 321 - 336." type="journal article" year="1890">
Faust (
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FD11FC53FCA3FDE3" box="[711,779,525,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1890.0">1890</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the new name 
<taxonomicName id="4C7982BEFF8FC506FC0FFC53FB6AFDE2" box="[985,1218,525,550]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Broconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="B90D252FFF8FC506FC0FFC53FB6AFDE2" box="[985,1218,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Broconius helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF8FC506FF41FC6CFDFFFD88" author="Alonso-Zarazaga" box="[151,599,562,588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C. (1999) A World Catalogue of Families and Genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (Excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae). Entomopraxis, S. C. P. Edition, Barcelona, 315 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Alonso-Zarazaga &amp; Lyal (
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FE07FC6CFDBAFD88" box="[465,530,562,588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1999.0">1999</number>
: 
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FDC8FC6CFDE7FD88" box="[542,591,562,588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="189.0">189</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Moreover 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE884CCFF8FC506FD37FC6CFC1BFD88" author="Hoffmann" box="[737,947,562,588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" refString="Hoffmann, A. (1954) Description de dix nouveaux Curculionides de la region palearctique. (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 59 (4): 50 - 54." type="journal article" year="1954">
Hoffmann (
<number id="3DB1EB1AFF8FC506FCBAFC6CFC02FD88" box="[876,938,562,588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1954.0">1954</number>
)
